						<div class="postbody">That's sort of what I thought. <br /><br />I set up a collision table to handle screen00 and got it working exactly as I wanted to.  <br /><br />Now, with my screen changes (working, using a nametable pointer to load the next screen), I also want to change the collision table (so I'm attempting to set up a collisionPointer that will work parallel).<br /><br />The values are simple hex values (right now, either #$01, #$02, or #$03).  This is what I've done to set up the table.<br /><br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent"><br />;; there is a variable called tileInfo<br />;; CollisionPointers contains the various data tables,<br />;;named CollisionDataTable01, CollisionDataTable02..etc...<br /><br />LoadCollisionTable:<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; LDA newScreen&nbsp; ;;right now, this is loading #$05<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; TAX<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; LDA CollisionPointers, X&nbsp; ;;<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; STA tileInfo<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; LDX #$FF<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; LDY #$00<br /><br />LoadCollisionLoop:<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; STA tileInfo,y<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; INY<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; DEX<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; BNE LoadCollisionLoop<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; RTS<br /><br /></div><br /><br />So now, I should be able to get the tileInfo using my method by using LDA tileInfo,y, correct?<br /><br />Again, I know the codes for the collision are working fine...when it was just a single table rather than a pointer, everything worked ok.  Now, things are funky.  <br /><br />See any glaring reason that might be based on the above?<br /><br />Thanks</div>

