					<br /><b>Joined:</b> Sun Jan 22, 2012 12:03 pm<br /><b>Posts:</b> 2176<br /><b>Location:</b> Canada
				</span>

			</td>
			<td valign="top">
				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">On the 6502, you have a 16-bit address space. This means that pointers to that space are 2 bytes in size. Your &quot;CollisionPointers&quot; array needs to store 2-byte addresses, and you've only loaded a single byte from it.<br /><br />That's the first mistake.<br /><br />The second mistake is STA tileInfo, Y.<br /><br />As I just mentioned, tileInfo should be the address of a 2-byte pointer, not a single byte, but beyond that problem, STA tileInfo, Y does not follow the pointer. STA tileInfo, Y will store at tileInfo itself, which will overwrite your pointer, and then the data after it as Y continues to increment.<br /><br />You want: STA (tileInfo), Y<br /><br />This looks up the address pointed to by the 2-byte pointer data stored at tileInfo, then adds Y to it, then stores A there.<br /><br />Read this: <a href="http://www.obelisk.demon.co.uk/6502/addressing.html" class="postlink">http://www.obelisk.demon.co.uk/6502/addressing.html</a><br /><br />Refer to that page whenever you forget. Eventually you will remember it.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

						<table width="100%" cellspacing="0">
						<tr valign="middle">
							<td class="gensmall" align="right">
							
							</td>
						</tr>
						</table>
					</td>
				</tr>
				</table>
			</td>
		</tr>

